# Documentation

See `docs` for project-specific information that should be referenced frequently.

## Rules

- JSDoc for all public functions/types/classes
- Document "why" not "what"
- Update docs when code changes
- Use examples
- Remove outdated comments
- Be specific (avoid vague terms)
- Document assumptions

## JSDoc Format

````typescript
/**
 * Creates a new resource.
 *
 * @param input - Resource parameters
 * @param input.name - Name of the resource
 * @returns Resource object with ok status
 * @throws {TRPCError} NOT_FOUND - Resource not found
 * @throws {TRPCError} FORBIDDEN - Insufficient permissions
 *
 * @example
 * ```typescript
 * const result = await api.resources.create({ name: "Example" });
 * ```
 */
export async function createResource(input: { name: string }) {
  // Implementation
}
````

